display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> distinct elements into <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m]]></fr:tex> non-empty, non-overlapping, indistinguishable subsets. Denote it as <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S(n, m)]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\left \{ n \atop  m \right \}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p><fr:strong>Recurrence Relation</fr:strong>:

  <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[     S(n, m) = mS(n - 1, m) + S(n - 1, m - 1)   ]]></fr:tex>

  <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[     S(n, 0) = [n = 0]   ]]></fr:tex></fr:p><fr:p><fr:strong>General Formula</fr:strong>:

  <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[     S(n, m) = \frac {1}{m!} \sum _{i = 0}^{m} (-1)^{m - i} \binom {m}{i} i^n   ]]></fr:tex></fr:p><fr:p><fr:strong>Mathematica Code</fr:strong>:

  
  <fr:pre><fr:code>StirlingS2[n, m]</fr:code></fr:pre></fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter><fr:tree
